AMEREN ILLINOIS COMPANY
RATE SCHEDULE FTS FIRM TRANSPORTATION SERVICE
1. AVAILABILITY 1.1 This Rate Schedule is available for the Transportation of Gas on a firm basis by Ameren Illinois Company (hereinafter referred to as Transporter) for any party (hereinafter referred to as Shipper), under the following conditions: (a) Shipper submits a valid request as defined in Section 7 of the General Terms and Conditions of the Statement of Operating Conditions and enters into a contract with Transporter for Rate Schedule FTS service in the form of the service agreement (FTS Agreement) set forth in the Statement of Operating Conditions; (b) Transporter determines that sufficient available and uncommitted capacity exists on its system or parts thereof (including receipt and delivery points) to perform the firm Transportation service requested. Firm service shall not be available from Transporter if capacity on the pipeline segment(s), Point(s) of Receipt, or Point(s) of Delivery has been fully committed to other Shipper(s); (c) Shipper's receipt points are limited to Gas production sources connected to Transporter's system; and (d) Shipper and Transporter have executed an agreement for the construction and interconnection of any facilities needed to provide the requested service, consistent with Section 17 of the General Terms and Conditions of the Statement of Operating Conditions. 2. APPLICABILITY AND CHARACTER OF SERVICE 2.1 This rate schedule shall apply to the Transportation of Gas by Transporter pursuant to an FTS Agreement executed by Transporter and Shipper providing for Transportation service each day on a firm basis up to the Maximum Daily Quantity (MDQ) and shall be subject to the provisions of the FTS Agreement, this Rate Schedule FTS, and the General Terms and Conditions. 2.2 Service hereunder shall consist of: (a) the receipt of daily quantities of Gas by Transporter from Shipper plus Fuel Use and LUFG at the Point(s) of Receipt up to the MDQ specified in the FTS Agreement as are nominated by Shipper and scheduled by Transporter pursuant to Section 8 of the General Terms and Conditions; (b) the Transportation of such quantities of Gas by Transporter under the terms of this rate schedule and the General Terms and Conditions; and (c) the delivery to Shipper or for Shipper's account at the Point(s) of Delivery thermally equivalent quantities of Gas equal to the quantities received less applicable Fuel Use and LUFG. 2.3 Service provided by Transporter under this rate schedule shall be firm and shall not be subject to curtailment, interruption or discontinuance, except as specified in Section 8 of the General Terms and Conditions. 2.4 Quantities in excess of Shipper's MDQ as are nominated by Shipper and scheduled by Transporter pursuant to Section 8 of the General Terms and Conditions shall be authorized and transported by Transporter only when capacity is available on Transporter's Pipeline System and the provision of such service shall not adversely affect other Shipper's rights. All authorized overrun service is Interruptible in nature and is subject to curtailment or interruption as provided in Section 8 of the General Terms and Conditions. 2.5 Requests for firm service shall be accepted and capacity assigned if Transporter determines, following its review and evaluation of a completed request, that all conditions of Section 1 of this Rate Schedule have been met, including the condition that sufficient available and uncommitted capacity exists to perform the requested services on a firm basis, and that service can be provided consistent with the General Terms and Conditions of the Statement of Operating Conditions. Transporter shall make such determinations based on its assessment of overall system operations and requirements utilizing consistent and objective engineering and operational criteria. If insufficient capacity exists to meet all pending requests to enter into or amend existing firm Service Agreements, Transporter shall assess the relative engineering suitability and economic value to Transporter of the requested services to determine the priority. Transporter's evaluation of total economic value shall consider rate, quantity, term, operational impacts and maximization of overall system utilization. 3. RECEIPT AND DELIVERY POINTS 3.1 Shipper shall tender all Gas at the Point(s) of Receipt specified in Shipper's FTS Agreement. 3.2 Transporter shall tender all Gas to be delivered to Shipper at the Point(s) of Delivery as specified in Shipper's FTS Agreement. 3.3 Transporter and Shipper may add or delete Receipt and Delivery Point(s) to the FTS Agreement from time to time by mutual agreement, subject to the terms of Section 7 of the General Terms and Conditions, provided Transporter determines that it has sufficient available and uncommitted capacity to provide service at such point(s) on a firm basis. Unless Transporter agrees otherwise, the applicable monthly reservation charge shall not be reduced by a change to the Receipt or Delivery Point(s). 3.4 Shipper shall be responsible for Transportation upstream of the Point(s) of Receipt and downstream from the Point(s) of Delivery and for the payment of all Transportation charges related thereto. Transporter shall have no liability for any upstream or downstream Transportation. 4. RATES AND CHARGES 4.1 Transporter has elected to provide 18 C.F.R. 284.224 Transportation service utilizing the rates approved by the FERC pursuant to 18 C.F.R. 284.123 (b)(2)(i). All charges for Transportation service under this rate schedule shall be stated on the Statement of Currently Effective Rates sheet of the Statement of Operating Conditions on file with the FERC. 4.2 For all service rendered under this rate schedule, Shipper shall pay Transporter each month the sum of the following: (a) Reservation Charge - A monthly charge equal to the product of the applicable monthly reservation rate(s) and Shipper's MDQ; (b) Usage Charge - A volumetric charge equal to the product of the applicable usage rate(s) and the total quantities of natural gas delivered by Transporter to Point(s) of Delivery during the billing month; (c) Authorized Overrun Charge - A volumetric charge equal to the product of the applicable overrun rate and any overrun quantities authorized and transported by Transporter during the billing month; and (d) Other Fees and Charges - Other fees, charges, and penalties which may be assessed as provided by the Statement of Operating Conditions or which may be permitted by the FERC. (e) All sales, use, excise or other such taxes and fees that are legally effective and applicable to the service provided. 4.3 Fuel and Lost and Unaccounted For (LUFG) Retention. Transporter shall retain applicable Fuel Use and LUFG in kind. The amount of Gas for Fuel Use and LUFG is determined in accordance with Section 8 of the General Terms and Conditions. 4.4 Transporter may on a not unduly discriminatory basis agree to discount the reservation charge below the otherwise applicable maximum rate. 4.5 Discounted Rates. Unless otherwise agreed by Transporter, Transporter shall have no obligation to offer its services at rates less than its currently effective maximum rates. Transporter may at any time and from time to time agree to charge an amount less than the currently effective maximum rate(s) for service(s) provided to a Shipper. Transporter shall not apply this provision in an unduly discriminatory manner, or in a manner contrary to FERC's regulations. 4.6 Partial Month's Service. In the event the date on which Transporter places its monthly Transportation charge in effect occurs on any day other than the first day of a month, then the monthly reservation charge for such month shall include only the number of days that Transportation service was in effect during such month. 4.7 Rate Adjustment. It is agreed that Transporter may make such adjustments to the Transportation rates provided herein as necessary to assure Transporter fair and equitable rates and may make such changes to this Statement of Operating Conditions as necessary to assure reasonable terms hereunder, subject to approval by the FERC or other governing body having authority, if any be required. 5. MINIMUM MONTHLY BILL 5.1 The minimum monthly bill shall be the Reservation Charge specified in Section 4.2 (a) of this rate schedule. 6. STATEMENT OF OPERATING CONDITIONS 6.1 The provisions of the General Terms and Conditions, as such provisions may be amended from time to time, are hereby incorporated by reference and made a part of this Rate Schedule FTS, and shall apply to service rendered hereunder, as though stated herein. If and to the extent the provisions of this rate schedule conflict with the provisions of said General Terms and Conditions, the provisions of this Rate Schedule shall prevail. 7. TITLE TO GAS 7.1 Title to all Gas delivered by Shipper to Transporter for Transportation under this rate schedule shall remain with Shipper at all times during Transportation by Transporter.

AMEREN ILLINOIS COMPANY RATE SCHEDULE ITS INTERRUPTIBLE TRANSPORTATION SERVICE
1. AVAILABILITY 1.1 This Rate Schedule is available for the Transportation of Gas on an interruptible basis by Ameren Illinois Company (hereinafter Transporter) for any party (hereinafter referred to as Shipper), under the following conditions: (a) Shipper submits a valid request as defined in Section 7 of the General Terms and Conditions of the Statement of Operating Conditions and enters into a contract with Transporter for Rate Schedule ITS service in the form of the service agreement (ITS Agreement) set forth in the Statement of Operating Conditions; and (b) Shipper and Transporter have executed an agreement for the construction and interconnection of any facilities needed to provide the requested service, consistent with Section 17 of the General Terms and Conditions of the Statement of Operating Conditions.
2. APPLICABILITY AND CHARACTER OF SERVICE 2.1 This rate schedule shall apply to the Transportation of Gas by Transporter pursuant to an ITS Agreement executed by Transporter and Shipper providing for Transportation service each day on an interruptible basis up to the Maximum Daily Quantity (MDQ) and shall be subject to the provisions of the ITS Agreement, this Rate Schedule ITS and the General Terms and Conditions. 2.2 Service hereunder shall consist of: (a) the receipt of such quantities of Gas by Transporter for Shipper's account at the Point(s) of Receipt specified in the ITS Agreement at times when system capacity is available for the Transportation of the quantities nominated by Shipper and scheduled by Transporter pursuant to Section 8 of the General Terms and Conditions plus Fuel Use and LUFG, up to the MDQ; (b) the Transportation of such quantities of Gas by Transporter under the terms of this rate schedule and the General Terms and Conditions of the Statement of Operating Conditions; and (c) the delivery to Shipper or for Shipper's account at the Point(s) of Delivery of thermally equivalent quantities of Gas equal to the quantities received, less applicable Fuel Use and LUFG. 2.3 Service provided by Transporter under this rate schedule shall be rendered on an interruptible basis and shall be subject to allocation of capacity and curtailment procedures as set forth in Section 8 of the General Terms and Conditions. 2.4 Service hereunder is subject to interruption by Transporter, without liability, as set forth in Section 8 of the General Terms and Conditions and may be interrupted whenever necessary to provide State regulated service, a higher priority service, or to maintain the integrity of Transporter's system or any part thereof. 3. RECEIPT AND DELIVERY POINTS 3.1 Each Shipper under this rate schedule shall be permitted to utilize all of Transporter's delivery points eligible for service provided pursuant to 18 C.F.R. 284.224. 3.2 Shipper shall be responsible for Transportation upstream of Point(s) of Receipt and downstream of Point(s) of Delivery and for the payment of all Transportation charges related thereto. Transporter shall have no liability for any upstream or downstream Transportation charges. 4. RATES AND CHARGES 4.1 Transporter has elected to provide 18 C.F.R. 284.224 Transportation services utilizing the rates approved by the FERC Pursuant to 18 C.F.R. 284.123 (b)(2)(i). All charges for Transportation service under this rate schedule shall be stated on the Statement of Currently Effective Rates sheet of the Statement of Operating Conditions on file with FERC. 4.2 For all service rendered under this rate schedule, Shipper shall pay Transporter the sum of the following: (a) Usage Charge - A volumetric charge equal to the product of the applicable usage rate(s) and the total quantities of natural gas delivered by Transporter to the Point(s) of Delivery during the billing month; or (b) Authorized Overrun Charge - A charge equal to the product of the applicable overrun rate and any overrun quantities authorized and transported by Transporter during the billing month; and (c) Other Fees and Charges - Other fees, charges, and penalties which may be assessed as provided by the Statement of Operating Conditions or which may be permitted by FERC. (d) All sales, use, excise or other such taxes and fees that are legally effective and applicable to the service provided. 4.3 Fuel Use and Lost and Unaccounted For (LUFG) Reimbursement. Transporter shall retain applicable Fuel Use and LUFG in kind. The amount of Gas for Fuel Use and LUFG is determined in accordance with Section 8 of the General Terms and Conditions. 4.4 Transporter may on a not unduly discriminatory basis agree to discount the rate for service under this rate schedule below the applicable maximum rate. 4.5 Discounted Rates. Unless otherwise agreed by Transporter, Transporter shall have no obligation to offer its services at rates less than its currently effective maximum rates. Transporter may at any time and from time to time agree to charge an amount less than the currently effective maximum rate(s) for service(s) provided to a Shipper. Transporter shall not apply this provision in an unduly discriminatory manner, or in a manner contrary to FERC's regulations. 4.6 Rate Adjustment. It is agreed that Transporter may make such adjustments to the Transportation rates provided herein as necessary to assure Transporter fair and equitable rates and may make such changes to this Statement of Operating Conditions as necessary to assure reasonable terms hereunder, subject to approval by the FERC or other governing body having authority, if any be required. 5. STATEMENT OF OPERATING CONDITIONS 5.1 The provisions of the General Terms and Conditions of the Statement of Operating Conditions, as such provisions may be amended from time to time, are hereby incorporated by reference and made a part of this Rate Schedule ITS, and shall apply to service rendered hereunder, as though stated herein. If and to the extent the provisions of this rate schedule conflict with the provisions of said General Terms and Conditions, the provisions of this rate schedule shall prevail. 6. TITLE TO GAS 6.1 Title to all Gas delivered by Shipper to Transporter for Transportation under this rate schedule shall remain with Shipper at all times during Transportation by Transporter.
